  "prompt": "Are beautiful-looking girls always harder to chase compared to ordinary-looking ones?",
  "response": "The perception of beauty and the dynamics of attraction can vary widely from person to person. While some may find that attractive individuals are harder to pursue due to factors like heightened attention, confidence, or social expectations, others may not experience the same challenges. \n\nBeautiful individuals might attract more attention, which could lead to them being more selective in their dating choices. Additionally, societal standards often place a higher level of scrutiny on them, which can affect their interpersonal interactions. However, chasing someone involves personal connection, shared interests, and compatibility, which can transcend physical appearance.\n\nUltimately, individual experiences and preferences vary, and there is no definitive rule that applies universally. Building genuine connections based on mutual respect and understanding is often more important than looks alone.",
